{
  "lab_description": "Digital IC frontend design for AI accelerators and high-performance computing, with broad interest in emerging compute paradigms and cross-layer system innovations. Core expertise covers matrix multiplication (GEMM) engines, Tensor Core microarchitecture, Vector/SIMD units, systolic arrays, and MAC datapaths. Extended interests include: (1) hardware for LLM/Transformer inference and training (KV-cache management, MoE routing, attention acceleration); (2) advanced packaging and chiplet integration for scalable AI systems (UCIe, 3D IC, HBM/PIM integration); (3) novel arithmetic and low-precision formats (MXFP, block floating-point, logarithmic systems, custom FP formats beyond IEEE-754); (4) design methodology and hardware generation (Chisel/SpinalHDL, HLS, parametric RTL generators, formal verification, equivalence checking); (5) resilient and secure compute (process variation, aging, voltage noise, side-channel resistance); (6) spatial and dataflow architectures, CGRA, event-driven/async logic; (7) memory-centric computing (near-memory, in-memory, processing-using-memory with emerging devices like ReRAM/MRAM). Target platforms: ASIC, FPGA, advanced nodes (FinFET/GAA). Relevant to computer architecture, VLSI, arithmetic circuits, accelerator microarchitecture, and emerging device integration.",
  
